args: I sure am! Nice to see you again.
Can I get the usual, please?
Certainly. Let's get that sword\nof yours sharpened.
Now for the finishing touch...\nTime to drink your mana!
(...I cannot get enough of that smile!)
There, all done! You should think twice\nabout getting it sharpened every day,\nthough. You'll soon have no sword left!
Well, if that happens,\nI'll just buy a new one!
Eh heh heh! This shop's weapons are\nmore than you can handle, young'un!
Eh heh heh! Well then, Rena,\nmight ya take a look at m'staff?
The metallic parts had started to loosen,\nso I tightened them up for you.
You're one in a million, Rena!\nSure wish I could talk ya into\nmarryin' m'grandson...
Ha ha! They do say the mind is\nthe first thing to go, old timer.
Hmph. I'm in perfect mental AND \nphysical health, I'll have ya know!
Say, Rena. Any way you can push\nthe price of this axe down a little?
I'm terribly sorry, but that's as low\nas I can go.
Aw, how can you say no to\na handsome face like this?
Handsome? You look like the wrong\nend of a mule! Now quit causing\ntrouble for Rena and leave already!
The lad's right! You got no business\nbein' in a store without knowin' what\nthe goods're worth!
You two don't know the first thing\nabout business. Now get outta\nmy face before this gets ugly!
All right, that's enough from all of you!
Ramona says she's run out of materials\nto work with, and she's suuuuper pissed.
Ah, I think I know what she needs.
She needn't worry—I saw we were \nrunning low and put in a new order.\nThey're waiting around back.
No, no... Oh, while you're here, we\nhave an empty spot on the sword shelf.\nCould you restock it from storage?
Lemme get Ramona what she needs\nso she stops boring holes in me with\nher eyes and I'll get right on it.
Looks like another busy day in here.
Oh, hello {player_name}!\nWhat can I do for you?
Nothing really. I was just curious how\neverything was going, so I thought I'd\npeek my head in and see.
Oh my. It's not very gentlemanly of you\nto be peeking on a young lady.
Er, yeah, I guess that came out wrong...\nStill, you DO run this place well.
You're very polite to all your customers,\nand you see and address issues with\nstock before they actually arise.

I'd pictured you being as laid-back here
as you are the rest of the time, but you
seem to run the place with an iron fist.
...Er, a KIND iron fist, mind you.
I'm honored to hear you say... Hmm?
I'm sorry, please give me a moment.
Did something catch your interest, sir?
What? No! I mean, yes! I mean...\nI don't know what you're implying!
Well, you clearly liked that dagger so\nmuch you placed it in your pocket.\nI'm honored!
Th-this dagger? No, th-this is mine!\nI've always had it!
Do you not want to test how sharp it is?\nIt can cut anything, you know...\nmuch like my own blade.
Okay, okay! I'll give it back!\nJust don't cut meeeee!
Oh, dear! Dropping it like that will\ndamage it!
You get a lot of shoplifters in here?
Occasionally. No doubt he was hoping\nto make a profit on the black market.
Ever since setting up shop in the Halidom,\nour weapons have become rather popular.
So we must be careful that they\ndon't end up in the wrong hands.
After all, a weapon can be a tool for\ngood or evil depending on who wields it.
I don't want our goods to hurt people—\nI want them to be used by you.
You and your fight for peace!
I want you to make everyone happy...\nincluding me, one day.
If peace returns to this land, everyone will\nbe happy—and that includes me, right?
Oh! Riiiight. Yes, of course.\nThat...makes sense.
Well, just leave everything to me and I'll\nmake sure everyone can be happy again.
But I'll need the help of you and\nyour sisters to make that a reality.
And we won't hesitate to give it!
We'll make this land happy together!
